    "actor_description": "My heart slams into gear—no warning, just instant thunder in my chest. My breath goes shallow and rapid, pulling at air that won't fill my lungs. Everything sharpens into threats and exits. My thoughts fragment into one screaming loop: move move move—but my body can't parse which direction means safe. I'm wired to flee with nowhere to run.",
    "description_text": "{actor} snaps taut—body locked mid-motion, eyes blown wide and darting. Their breath comes in quick, shallow gasps, chest visibly stuttering. Hands flutter and clench at nothing, fingers seeking purchase on empty air. Their head whips in fractured scans, trying to track threats from every angle at once, movements jagged and incomplete.",
    "alternate_descriptions": {
        "auditory": "I hear breathing fractures into rapid, shallow pulls—air sucked in hard but never finishing the exhale. There's a choked, high sound caught in the throat, almost a whimper swallowed back. Movement sounds jerky, abrupt: fabric rustling in stops and starts, feet shifting without going anywhere, maybe a hand slapping or scraping against a surface searching for something solid."
